WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.972
[INTRO MUSIC]

00:00:07.395 --> 00:00:09.367
[APPLAUSE]

00:00:15.283 --> 00:00:16.690
DR. VINCE VITALE:
The alternative

00:00:16.690 --> 00:00:22.450
to fleeing from truth
is fighting for truth.

00:00:22.450 --> 00:00:25.690
I was walking around
Oxford a few months ago.

00:00:25.690 --> 00:00:28.770
And two guys walking
just ahead of me

00:00:28.770 --> 00:00:30.580
were having a
spirited conversation

00:00:30.580 --> 00:00:34.480
about how crazy they found
certain beliefs that they

00:00:34.480 --> 00:00:35.560
disagreed with.

00:00:35.560 --> 00:00:38.290
And one turned to
the other and said,

00:00:38.290 --> 00:00:43.300
maybe the only solution
would be to shame them out

00:00:43.300 --> 00:00:44.590
of their beliefs.

00:00:44.590 --> 00:00:47.350
And then, the other guy turned,
and this is what he said.

00:00:47.350 --> 00:00:48.370
I wrote it down.

00:00:48.370 --> 00:00:50.840
He said, "Yes, that's
what we should do.

00:00:50.840 --> 00:00:53.220
We should ridicule
them mercilessly

00:00:53.220 --> 00:00:57.360
in the most insensitive
ways we can think of."

00:00:57.360 --> 00:00:59.400
That's an exact quote.

00:00:59.400 --> 00:01:02.929
And then, they turned, and they
swiped their faculty cards,

00:01:02.929 --> 00:01:05.220
and walked into the University
of Oxford of Theoretical

00:01:05.220 --> 00:01:07.020
Physics building.

00:01:07.020 --> 00:01:10.800
These were probably scholars
at Oxford, a place that prides

00:01:10.800 --> 00:01:13.110
itself on intellectual freedom.

00:01:13.110 --> 00:01:16.830
And the exchange of ideas and
merciless, insensitive ridicule

00:01:16.830 --> 00:01:18.480
was the best that
they can come up

00:01:18.480 --> 00:01:22.480
with for how we should
resolve disagreements.

00:01:22.480 --> 00:01:24.720
I found myself wondering
how many beliefs they

00:01:24.720 --> 00:01:27.300
held in theoretical
physics that one day will

00:01:27.300 --> 00:01:30.120
be considered ridiculous.

00:01:30.120 --> 00:01:33.340
How does someone
get to this point?

00:01:33.340 --> 00:01:35.580
How does someone
get to the point

00:01:35.580 --> 00:01:41.670
where merciless ridicule seems
like the best way forward?

00:01:41.670 --> 00:01:47.960
I think it's because you come to
see truth as greater than love.

00:01:47.960 --> 00:01:51.750
If truth is greater than
love, then you fight.

00:01:51.750 --> 00:01:54.480
Then, the pursuit
of truth justifies

00:01:54.480 --> 00:01:57.720
whatever means necessary,
whether the means of Oxford

00:01:57.720 --> 00:02:01.110
academics or the
means of terrorists.

00:02:01.110 --> 00:02:05.610
The alternative is that
love is greater than truth.

00:02:05.610 --> 00:02:06.920
Then, you flee.

00:02:06.920 --> 00:02:09.150
You flee from the
dangers of truth,

00:02:09.150 --> 00:02:10.620
and accept every
belief, no matter

00:02:10.620 --> 00:02:13.620
how incoherent because at least
that's better than starting

00:02:13.620 --> 00:02:15.570
yourself on a trajectory
that, ultimately,

00:02:15.570 --> 00:02:19.120
is going to lead to intolerance,
extremism, and violence.

00:02:19.120 --> 00:02:21.750
The truth gets sacrificed
at the altar of love,

00:02:21.750 --> 00:02:24.070
or love gets sacrificed
at the altar of truth.

00:02:24.070 --> 00:02:25.740
Either truth is
greater than love,

00:02:25.740 --> 00:02:27.240
or love is greater than truth.

00:02:27.240 --> 00:02:28.500
Fight or flee.

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:31.860
This is the cultural ultimatum
that we're living in.

00:02:31.860 --> 00:02:34.800
What's your choice?

00:02:34.800 --> 00:02:38.630
And I don't think it's
getting any better.

00:02:38.630 --> 00:02:44.520
I had a graphic here
of a representation

00:02:44.520 --> 00:02:49.360
of our increasing political
polarization in this country.

00:02:49.360 --> 00:02:52.980
And when you see the difference
between 1994 and 2004,

00:02:52.980 --> 00:02:56.190
it's very minimal in terms
of our political values.

00:02:56.190 --> 00:02:57.720
And then, when you
see the widening

00:02:57.720 --> 00:03:03.120
of the gap between 2004
and 2014, it's huge.

00:03:03.120 --> 00:03:08.340
92% of Republicans are to the
right of the median Democrat.

00:03:08.340 --> 00:03:13.890
And 94% of Democrats are to the
left of the median Republican.

00:03:13.890 --> 00:03:16.540
We're not close enough
to talk to each other.

00:03:16.540 --> 00:03:18.420
And so, from that
distance, all you can do

00:03:18.420 --> 00:03:21.840
is either ignore each other,
or shout at each other.

00:03:21.840 --> 00:03:24.680
Once again, fight or flee.

00:03:24.680 --> 00:03:27.000
What's your choice?

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:30.080
Maybe there's another way.

00:03:30.080 --> 00:03:35.780
Hassan John was one of
my students last year.

00:03:35.780 --> 00:03:40.350
He's an Anglican minister
from northern Nigeria.

00:03:40.350 --> 00:03:44.110
And on the first day
of classes at lunch,

00:03:44.110 --> 00:03:47.680
one of his fellow classmates
said to him, Hassan,

00:03:47.680 --> 00:03:51.090
how do you manage to minister
in a context in which you're

00:03:51.090 --> 00:03:53.530
viewed as the enemy?

00:03:53.530 --> 00:03:55.930
We knew that Hassan
was from a region that

00:03:55.930 --> 00:03:58.030
was terrorized by Boko Haram.

00:03:58.030 --> 00:04:01.360
We found out only later that
he had been shot at twice

00:04:01.360 --> 00:04:04.540
and that there was a
bounty on his head.

00:04:04.540 --> 00:04:10.210
Hassan began to tell us a story
of how there came a point when

00:04:10.210 --> 00:04:14.710
he had seen so many of
his brothers and sisters

00:04:14.710 --> 00:04:17.380
murdered for their
faith that he started

00:04:17.380 --> 00:04:21.164
a conversation with a known
gun dealer to acquire an AK47.

00:04:21.164 --> 00:04:25.497
And he thought violence
was the only answer.

00:04:25.497 --> 00:04:27.330
When he was in his home
trying to figure out

00:04:27.330 --> 00:04:30.540
where to get the money
to acquire this gun,

00:04:30.540 --> 00:04:34.430
a young girl ran by the
front door of his home

00:04:34.430 --> 00:04:35.270
during school hours.

00:04:35.270 --> 00:04:37.520
He stopped her, and he said,
why aren't you in school?

00:04:37.520 --> 00:04:39.860
She said, my parents don't
have the money to pay.

00:04:39.860 --> 00:04:42.010
He said, that's not right.

00:04:42.010 --> 00:04:44.800
My church and I would like
to pay for your school fees.

00:04:44.800 --> 00:04:47.230
Will you take me
to your parents?

00:04:47.230 --> 00:04:50.860
And then, his stomach
knotted up as she walked him

00:04:50.860 --> 00:04:54.640
across the clear dividing line
between the Christian section

00:04:54.640 --> 00:04:56.620
of town and the Muslim
section of town.

00:04:56.620 --> 00:04:59.740
He had assumed that this girl
was from a Christian home.

00:04:59.740 --> 00:05:01.472
She was, in fact,
from a Muslim home.

00:05:01.472 --> 00:05:03.430
But he had committed to
paying her school fees,

00:05:03.430 --> 00:05:07.300
and so Hassan and his church
began to pay her school fees.

00:05:07.300 --> 00:05:09.520
Then, he found out that
her brothers were also

00:05:09.520 --> 00:05:10.660
not in school.

00:05:10.660 --> 00:05:13.300
Then, he met another Muslim
child who wasn't in school,

00:05:13.300 --> 00:05:14.650
and another, and another.

00:05:14.650 --> 00:05:17.140
Today, there are
200 Muslim children

00:05:17.140 --> 00:05:19.480
who are being educated
in church schools

00:05:19.480 --> 00:05:21.550
by Hassan and his church.

00:05:21.550 --> 00:05:23.500
Then Hassan thought
to himself, why are we

00:05:23.500 --> 00:05:24.940
only helping the children?

00:05:24.940 --> 00:05:27.834
He realized that the
women in his community

00:05:27.834 --> 00:05:30.250
had a style of making clothes
that the Muslim women didn't

00:05:30.250 --> 00:05:30.700
have.

00:05:30.700 --> 00:05:32.491
And the Muslim women
had a style of cooking

00:05:32.491 --> 00:05:34.630
that the Christian
women didn't have.

00:05:34.630 --> 00:05:37.600
And now there are 160
Christian and Muslim women

00:05:37.600 --> 00:05:39.940
who get together, and
share their expertise,

00:05:39.940 --> 00:05:43.030
and befriend each other,
and bless each other.

00:05:43.030 --> 00:05:46.600
Just before Hassan
came to Oxford,

00:05:46.600 --> 00:05:50.200
some militant youths who
are involved in terrorism

00:05:50.200 --> 00:05:53.030
showed up at his front door.

00:05:53.030 --> 00:05:54.370
And he was scared.

00:05:54.370 --> 00:05:56.660
He thought his
life was in danger.

00:05:56.660 --> 00:05:59.100
He thought his family's
life was in danger.

00:05:59.100 --> 00:06:04.360
And they looked at him sternly,
and they said, why don't you

00:06:04.360 --> 00:06:06.070
do anything for us?

00:06:06.070 --> 00:06:07.420
You help the children.

00:06:07.420 --> 00:06:08.680
You help the women.

00:06:08.680 --> 00:06:10.840
Why don't you do
anything for us?

00:06:10.840 --> 00:06:14.050
Militant youth engaged
in terrorism are showing

00:06:14.050 --> 00:06:17.050
[? up at the ?] [? door ?] of
an Anglican pastor asking him

00:06:17.050 --> 00:06:20.470
to incorporate them into
his mission strategy.

00:06:20.470 --> 00:06:23.230
Absolutely unbelievable.

00:06:23.230 --> 00:06:25.630
And here's my question.

00:06:25.630 --> 00:06:31.170
Why did those youth
respond so positively?

00:06:31.170 --> 00:06:35.190
After all, Hassan was
disagreeing with them

00:06:35.190 --> 00:06:35.960
in a big way.

00:06:35.960 --> 00:06:39.240
For starters, he was
saying that Jesus Christ

00:06:39.240 --> 00:06:42.270
should be at the center
of their education.

00:06:42.270 --> 00:06:45.067
He was also clearly saying that
we should love our enemies,

00:06:45.067 --> 00:06:46.650
we should turn the
other cheek, and we

00:06:46.650 --> 00:06:48.274
should pray for those
who persecute us,

00:06:48.274 --> 00:06:51.690
things that would not have
been true in their world view.

00:06:51.690 --> 00:06:53.560
But here's the thing.

00:06:53.560 --> 00:06:56.670
Hassan's disagreement
with them was not

00:06:56.670 --> 00:06:58.940
greater than his love for them.

00:06:58.940 --> 00:07:03.450
His loving sacrifice for
them was the very content

00:07:03.450 --> 00:07:05.310
of his disagreement with them.

00:07:05.310 --> 00:07:10.500
He cut the link between
disagreement and devaluing

00:07:10.500 --> 00:07:14.550
of the person because his
communication of truth

00:07:14.550 --> 00:07:19.860
was one and the same as
his communication of love.

00:07:19.860 --> 00:07:21.910
And that is the gospel.

00:07:21.910 --> 00:07:25.930
That is the central
message of Christianity.

00:07:25.930 --> 00:07:28.330
Jesus disagreed with us.

00:07:28.330 --> 00:07:31.930
His very coming was an act
of disagreement with us.

00:07:31.930 --> 00:07:35.230
A statement that we required
saving because our lives

00:07:35.230 --> 00:07:39.760
disagreed so badly with what
He had intended for them.

00:07:39.760 --> 00:07:47.150
But Jesus' coming was also his
greatest act of love for us.

00:07:47.150 --> 00:07:50.090
His willingness to
suffer alongside us.

00:07:50.090 --> 00:07:53.120
His willingness to
join us in our shame.

00:07:53.120 --> 00:07:56.540
His willingness to lay
down His life for us.

00:07:56.540 --> 00:08:00.350
The cross where Jesus died,
this symbol of Christianity.

00:08:00.350 --> 00:08:04.760
It's a symbol of the perfect
intersection of love and truth.

00:08:04.760 --> 00:08:06.950
Jesus's death is the
greatest expression

00:08:06.950 --> 00:08:09.050
of God's disagreement with us.

00:08:09.050 --> 00:08:12.680
And yet, simultaneously, it
is the greatest expression

00:08:12.680 --> 00:08:14.150
of God's love for us.

00:08:14.150 --> 00:08:22.670
Truth and love perfectly
united in a personal sacrifice.

00:08:22.670 --> 00:08:24.830
Not truth is greater than love.

00:08:24.830 --> 00:08:28.790
Not love is greater than truth.

00:08:28.790 --> 00:08:31.440
But God is love.

00:08:31.440 --> 00:08:33.840
And God is truth.

00:08:33.840 --> 00:08:37.799
And therefore, truth is love.

00:08:37.799 --> 00:08:42.280
In Jesus, truth equals love.

00:08:42.280 --> 00:08:46.090
And therefore, I think
Jesus is uniquely positioned

00:08:46.090 --> 00:08:50.880
to get us out of the cultural
ultimatum that we're stuck in.

00:08:50.880 --> 00:08:52.940
Fight or flee.

00:08:55.610 --> 00:08:59.710
Authentic Christianity
rejects that ultimatum.

00:08:59.710 --> 00:09:02.720
It refuses to let
disagreement lead

00:09:02.720 --> 00:09:05.000
to the devaluing of the other.

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:08.690
It refuses to choose
between truth and love

00:09:08.690 --> 00:09:11.490
because, according to Jesus,
and in the person of Jesus,

00:09:11.490 --> 00:09:16.510
and in His sacrifice, truth
and love are one in the same.

00:09:16.510 --> 00:09:19.440
On one of his last
Sunday's with us in Oxford,

00:09:19.440 --> 00:09:22.900
our pastor interviewed Hassan.

00:09:22.900 --> 00:09:28.007
And his first question was, he
asked Hassan, is it worth it?

00:09:28.007 --> 00:09:30.340
And Hassan had this, sort of,
quizzical look on his face

00:09:30.340 --> 00:09:32.770
because the answer
was so obvious to him.

00:09:32.770 --> 00:09:34.770
And he said, of course.

00:09:34.770 --> 00:09:36.990
And then, our
pastor asked Hassan

00:09:36.990 --> 00:09:39.810
if he had any parting
words for us as a church.

00:09:39.810 --> 00:09:42.260
And he said that he did.

00:09:42.260 --> 00:09:44.830
And then he said,
I beg you, do not

00:09:44.830 --> 00:09:48.280
compromise here in
the West on the faith

00:09:48.280 --> 00:09:51.400
that we, in Africa,
are dying for.

00:09:51.400 --> 00:09:54.970
Do not compromise here
in the West on the faith

00:09:54.970 --> 00:09:57.910
that we, in Africa,
are dying for.

00:09:57.910 --> 00:10:01.620
And I personally have
to keep reminding myself

00:10:01.620 --> 00:10:05.670
that this is not
extraordinary Christianity.

00:10:05.670 --> 00:10:08.670
This is just the simple
message of Jesus.

00:10:08.670 --> 00:10:12.060
Truth that is of love,
love that is truth.

00:10:12.060 --> 00:10:16.140
Laying down your life in
order to communicate the truth

00:10:16.140 --> 00:10:17.910
to others.

00:10:17.910 --> 00:10:20.900
Who are you laying
down your life for?

00:10:20.900 --> 00:10:26.100
Every Christian needs to be
able to answer that question.

00:10:26.100 --> 00:10:30.810
How often is our disagreement
with others our very act

00:10:30.810 --> 00:10:34.050
of giving our lives for them?

00:10:34.050 --> 00:10:37.050
What would that look
like in our context?

00:10:37.050 --> 00:10:40.230
What would it look
like for us to disagree

00:10:40.230 --> 00:10:43.260
with people with
such generosity,

00:10:43.260 --> 00:10:45.990
and such love, and
such personal sacrifice

00:10:45.990 --> 00:10:47.970
that the people we're
disagreeing with

00:10:47.970 --> 00:10:50.310
would show up on
our front doorstep,

00:10:50.310 --> 00:10:53.940
as they did with Hassan,
asking for us to act

00:10:53.940 --> 00:10:57.130
on our disagreement with them?

00:10:57.130 --> 00:11:01.450
Who do you disagree
with passionately?

00:11:01.450 --> 00:11:04.700
Who's your enemy?

00:11:04.700 --> 00:11:08.480
I wonder if someone just
jumped into your mind

00:11:08.480 --> 00:11:11.180
as I asked those questions.

00:11:11.180 --> 00:11:12.290
Are you fighting them?

00:11:14.930 --> 00:11:18.950
Are you fleeing from them?

00:11:18.950 --> 00:11:23.830
Or are you making a
personal sacrifice for them?

00:11:23.830 --> 00:11:27.550
What would it look like
to communicate truth

00:11:27.550 --> 00:11:33.340
to those we disagree with
through an act of radical love

00:11:33.340 --> 00:11:35.710
and personal sacrifice?

00:11:35.710 --> 00:11:37.840
That is the question.

00:11:37.840 --> 00:11:39.850
I don't think that's
an easy question.

00:11:39.850 --> 00:11:43.420
But that is the question
that Hassan figured out

00:11:43.420 --> 00:11:47.990
how to answer in his context.

00:11:47.990 --> 00:11:49.670
And I think we will
live in brokenness

00:11:49.670 --> 00:11:52.310
until we can figure
out how to answer

00:11:52.310 --> 00:11:55.490
that question in our context.

00:11:55.490 --> 00:11:59.210
We're being told that we
live in a post truth society

00:11:59.210 --> 00:12:02.490
that, truth is dead.

00:12:02.490 --> 00:12:05.100
I don't think that
truth is dead.

00:12:05.100 --> 00:12:08.080
But I do think that truth died.

00:12:08.080 --> 00:12:15.790
2000 years ago on a wooden
cross, the truth was stretched,

00:12:15.790 --> 00:12:20.410
the truth was twisted,
and it was bent.

00:12:20.410 --> 00:12:25.700
The truth hurt, and
the truth was buried.

00:12:25.700 --> 00:12:32.180
Love and truth is at the central
message of the Christian faith.

00:12:32.180 --> 00:12:37.850
Love and truth find their
unity and their power

00:12:37.850 --> 00:12:41.290
in personal sacrifice.

00:12:41.290 --> 00:12:47.530
And there's only one God who
has sacrificed himself for us.

00:12:47.530 --> 00:12:51.140
And that's the God that
I commend to you today.

00:12:51.140 --> 00:12:53.216
[INAUDIBLE] brief word
of prayer with me.

00:13:00.960 --> 00:13:05.280
God, I thank you that I can
come to you with such confidence

00:13:05.280 --> 00:13:06.770
that you are both
love and truth.

00:13:09.580 --> 00:13:14.330
I thank you that when you
came and made a sacrifice

00:13:14.330 --> 00:13:17.020
that you didn't have to make.

00:13:17.020 --> 00:13:20.560
You told me the
truth about myself.

00:13:20.560 --> 00:13:24.220
You convinced me of
the evil in my heart

00:13:24.220 --> 00:13:26.930
because people just
like me killed you.

00:13:29.500 --> 00:13:33.100
And yet, simultaneously,
you convinced me

00:13:33.100 --> 00:13:35.470
of your love for me
because you showed me

00:13:35.470 --> 00:13:38.500
that there was nothing
that you wouldn't give,

00:13:38.500 --> 00:13:42.220
even your very
life, that I might

00:13:42.220 --> 00:13:44.260
be in friendship
and relationship

00:13:44.260 --> 00:13:47.530
with you for all eternity.

00:13:47.530 --> 00:13:51.010
And God, if that vision
of love and truth

00:13:51.010 --> 00:13:54.040
perfectly intersecting in
perfect unity that is true

00:13:54.040 --> 00:14:01.130
only in you, if there's anyone
in this room who doesn't know

00:14:01.130 --> 00:14:05.840
that possibility, who has
felt like they need to choose,

00:14:05.840 --> 00:14:08.270
I pray that today
would be a day where

00:14:08.270 --> 00:14:11.660
that vision of who you are,
perfect love and perfect truth,

00:14:11.660 --> 00:14:13.610
would settle deep
within our souls

00:14:13.610 --> 00:14:15.230
and would bring transformation.

00:14:15.230 --> 00:14:16.440
I trust you for that.

00:14:16.440 --> 00:14:17.610
In Jesus' name, amen.

00:14:25.035 --> 00:14:26.520
[APPLAUSE]

